&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Battle clerics are Ok, as long as they when there is a time to melee and when there is a time to be a healer. I for one will melee when on raids/ or going after a named where we have to clear halls, rooms, etc (basically on the move) All my melee is maxed out, and those summoned hammers can add more to the damage ratio, On a normal fight it (depending on group) could proc 10 times, making a thousand points of damage, stack with base melee hits it can add up to where you did some significant damage. If we are in a tough place where my tank is dropping bout as fast as my C-heal cast time, ya damn skippy im more on the heals and at this point dont have NOTHING, DPS wise in my spell gems....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I said it before on the other thread, I play the cleric to be a healer...I knew what I was getting into when I started my class, and have BIG hopes that I can hold that tittle of being the best healing class. Otherwise the charm of my purpose is gone, and I'm sure then i'll try other places..I Chose to play a cleric much like druids chose to play thier class. I knew from the beggining I most likely will always need a Tankable class to get anywhere in the game, I knew then Clerics was NOT the soloing type. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
