      <title>Re: Summit II Plans: Issue 2: The Secondary Role.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9497#M9497</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Saroc_Luclin wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;The problem with Complete heal is, you push one button, and you can not do anything else for 10 seconds. You can't move, you can't DPS, you can't alternate heal, you can't cure, you can't use an AA, you can't nuke, you can't stun, without interrupting that CHeal. It makes clerics a very monotonous class if that's all you see them as.&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;FONT color=#66cc00&gt;That is what balances cheal though.&amp;nbsp; Its high cast time balances against the low mana cost and makes the 9600HP heal worth doing.&amp;nbsp; It takes intelligence and skill to be able to cast cheal at the appropriate time.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;The CHeal playstyle is still around and will be around for a long while yet, but other playstyles are coming back too (or new ones developing). The Vie + regen cleric, the stunning cleric (need more work there to get the stuns back in line) and yes even the nuking cleric and the meeleeing cleric.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#66cc00&gt;I do all of the above and it's CHEAL that allows me to do these things.&amp;nbsp; Cheal gives me the extra mana to cast an RDS, my pet, nukes, and stuns (and DoTs soon too).&amp;nbsp; Cheal is what gives me time to actually get in some&amp;nbsp;damage.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#66cc00&gt;That may sound weird but its true; take a typical one minute fight, if I cast cheal 2 times in that fight that's 20 seconds out of 60, the other 40 seconds (that's two-thirds) I am able to melee, nuke, stun, RDS, etc.&amp;nbsp; I have to cast Hallowed Light 4 times during that same span of time (I tested in RSS), to keep the same tank alive. That's only&amp;nbsp;13 seconds worth of casting however, I have also spent nearly FOUR times the mana (800 vs 3100 base and since cheal IS affected by mana reduction effects they are neutralized), so I can't spend that mana nuking, or casting my pet, or the RDS.&amp;nbsp; All I can do is melee, and even then I have to sit out at times because I have reached a point where if I don't med between casts I will be oom shortly thereafter.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
