&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Try justifying the stand-back and heal style now.&amp;nbsp; I doubt it can be reasonably argued.&amp;nbsp; The only reason to stand-back and heal is if you feel you cannot do more than that.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The biggest obstacle facing clerics RIGHT NOW, is that we do not stack as a class AT ALL.&amp;nbsp; If there are two clerics in a group ONE is dead weight (we all know this).&amp;nbsp; The biggest obstacle we face in the apparent future (nothing is set in stone) is that other priest classes (Druids and Shamans) will soon be able to fill our role AND their current role as well, if that day has not arrived already. &amp;nbsp;Which means even ONE cleric in a group is dead weight.&amp;nbsp; This thread was intended to promote ideas for a secondary role a cleric can play.&amp;nbsp; Since (apparently) a LOT of us melee anyway, we suggested a way to improve that melee ability when our healing skill is not required.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;That being said, even if ALL the re-balancing is done chances are you will continure to see clerics getting groups for their healing abilities.&amp;nbsp; We are a KNOWN factor.&amp;nbsp; Everyone in EQ knows we can heal and we enjoy doing it.&amp;nbsp; Even if a group has a druid or shaman as a main healer I have little doubt that if a spot opened and a cleric was LFG they woudl take that cleric and shift the druid/shaman back to their "known" primary role.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Changing the subject somewhat: someone mentioned clerics with "slings".&amp;nbsp; This will not happen.&amp;nbsp; There are only five classes with range weapon capability in EQ (Ranger, Warrior, Paladin, Rogue, and Monk) If another class were to get a range attack it would be SK or Bard WAY before clerics.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;The notion of an offiensive stance could be remedied by "fixing" the divine avatar AA.&amp;nbsp; Right now, it does not last nearly long enough and its recast time is WAY too long to be of any real use.&amp;nbsp; Take off the regen, increase the duration and decrease the reuse time and it would be worth while.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;Improving our pet could go a LONG way to adding a role.&amp;nbsp; Part of a shaman's DPS at the moment comes from his/her pet and a shaman's ability to do a multi pet every so often.&amp;nbsp; The Cleric (and druid) pet is a JOKE.&amp;nbsp; If it cannot be retuned grant us AAs that will make it more permanent and improve its DPS.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
